%3EJulian%20Weber%2C%20the%20reigning%20European%20Games%20champion%20from%20Germany%2C%20has%20a%20personal%20best%20of%2089.54m.%20He%20is%20ranked%20third%20in%20the%20world%20and%20his%20season's%20best%20of%2088.37m%20came%20in%20May.%20In%202024%2C%20Weber%20has%20demonstrated%20remarkable%20consistency%2C%20competing%20in%20five%20tournaments%20and%20delivering%20throws%20exceeding%2085m%20in%20each%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOliver%20Helander%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOliver%20Helander%20of%20Finland%20is%20ranked%20fourth%20in%20the%20world%20and%20has%20a%20season's%20best%20of%2085.75m.%20He%20went%20head-to-head%20with%20Neeraj%20Chopra%20at%20the%20Paavo%20Nurmi%20Games%20earlier%20this%20year.%20Chopra%20had%20topped%20the%20event%20with%20a%20distance%20of%2085.97m%20while%20Helander%20was%20third%20with%20a%20distance%20of%2083.96m.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeshorn%20Walcott%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeshorn%20Walcott%20of%20Trinidad%20and%20Tobago%20will%20be%20gunning%20for%20his%20third%20Olympic%20medal%20in%20his%20fourth%20appearance.%20He%20won%20the%20gold%20medal%20at%20London%202012%2C%20bronze%20at%20Rio%202016%20and%20missed%20out%20at%20the%20Tokyo%202020%20Games.%20The%2031-year-old%20goes%20into%20the%20Olympics%20with%20a%20season-best%20of%2085.11m%20and%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20dark%20horse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeshorn%20Walcott%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJulius%20Yego%20of%20Kenya%2C%20the%20Rio%202016%20silver%20medallist%2C%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20dark%20horse%20as%20well.%20The%20former%20world%20champion%2C%20now%2035%2C%20has%20a%20season's%20best%20of%2081.74m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722919860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-