%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20who%20we%20are%20is%20defined%20by%20our%20personal%20lives%20so%20much%20more%20than%20our%20work%2C%20and%20we%20can%20be%20both%20of%20those%20things%20at%20once.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELively%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeople.com%2Fparents%2Fall-about-blake-lively-ryan-reynolds-children%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efour%20children%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20Ryan%20Reynolds%3A%20James%2C%209%2C%20Inez%2C%207%2C%20Betty%2C%204%2C%20and%20Olin%2C%201.%20Slate%20welcomed%20her%20first%20child%20%E2%80%94%20a%20daughter%20%E2%80%94%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BGossip%20Girl%26quot%3B%20star%20added%20that%20she%20sometimes%20finds%20it%20hard%20to%20manage%20the%20guilt%20she%20feels%20when%20she%20prioritizes%20one%20responsibility%20over%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20working%2C%20sometimes%20you%20feel%20guilty%20for%2C%20you%20know%2C%20not%20being%20in%20your%20personal%20life%20in%20those%20hours%20you're%20at%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Lively%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20when%20you're%20at%20work%2C%20you%20feel%20guilty%20by%20being%20distracted%20by%20wishing%20that%20you%20were%20at%20your%20personal%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20her%20busy%20schedule%2C%20Lively%20has%20worked%20out%20a%20way%20to%20carve%20out%20time%20for%20her%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20she%20revealed%20that%20she%20and%20Reynolds%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblake-lively-ryan-reynolds-work-parenting-kids-personal-life-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eagreed%20%26quot%3Bnot%20to%20work%20at%20the%20same%20time%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20they%20started%20dating%20so%20they%20could%20always%20prioritize%20their%20personal%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20not%20to%20have%20overlapping%20work%20schedules%20required%20a%20lot%20of%20effort%20to%20uphold%2C%20Lively%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThat%20takes%20working%20really%20hard%20when%20we're%20not.%20Just%20like%20financial%20planning%20and%20sustaining%20that%3B%20it%20takes%20balance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dc28ccf0-1912-4091-908f-5f2de3cbaafd%5C%22%3EManaging%20mom%20guilt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%202017%20survey%20of%20900%20participants%20conducted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goodto.com%2Ffamily%2Fmum-guilt-4212%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoodtoKnow%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20UK-based%20parenting%20site%2C%20found%20that%2078%25%20of%20mothers%20feel%20guilty%2C%20with%2068%25%20saying%20this%20occurred%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20day.%2061%25%20also%20said%20they%20compared%20themselves%20to%20other%20moms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20a%202015%20study%20has%20shown%20that%20children's%20academic%20and%20emotional%20well-being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2Fjomf.12170%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisn't%20necessarily%20dependent%20on%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20they%20spend%20with%20their%20mothers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20working%20moms%20everywhere%20still%20feel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-neurosurgeon-mom-demanding-job-parenting-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emom%20guilt%3C%2Fa%3E%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20working%20fathers%20are%20just%20as%20likely%20to%20feel%20the%20same%20way%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2015%2F04%2F01%2Fworking-mom-guilt-many-dads-feel-it-too%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2015%20Pew%20Research%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20with%20chronic%20guilt%20can%20have%20a%20serious%20impact%20on%20stress%20levels%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20causing%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20as%20well%20as%20increased%20blood%20pressure%2C%20according%20to%20