01975.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%20he%20was%20assassinated%20by%20a%20group%20of%20soldiers%20on%20August%2015%2C%20along%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20three%20sons.%20Khondaker%20Mostaq%20Ahmad%2C%20with%20the%20support%20of%20part%20of%20the%20army%2C%20then%20took%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmad's%20tenure%20was%20short-lived.%20He%20was%20overthrown%20in%20a%20coup%20instigated%20by%20the%20army's%20chief%20of%20staff%20Khaled%20Mosharraf%20on%20November%203%2C%20who%20was%20assassinated%20in%20turn%20by%20rival%20mutineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20series%20of%20further%20coups%20and%20counter-coups%2C%20General%20Ziaur%20Rahman%20took%20power%20on%20November%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1981-83%20%3A%20Bloody%20rebellion%2C%20bloodless%20coup%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20less%20than%20six%20years%20in%20power%2C%20Rahman%20was%20assassinated%20during%20an%20attempted%20revolt%20on%20May%2030%2C%201981.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20vice-president%20Abdus%20Sattar%20took%20over%20as%20interim%20president%20with%20the%20backing%20of%20General%20Hussain%20Muhammad%20Ershad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Ershad%20turned%20on%20Sattar%20within%20a%20year%2C%20ousting%20him%20in%20a%20bloodless%20coup%20on%20March%2024%2C%201982.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20takeover%2C%20he%20imposed%20martial%20law%20and%20installed%20Ahsanuddin%20Chowdhury%20as%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20on%20December%2011%2C%201983%2C%20Ershad%20proclaimed%20himself%20head%20of%20state.%20Chowdhury%2C%20whose%20position%20was%20honorary%2C%20went%20on%20to%20lead%20a%20political%20party%20loyal%20to%20the%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1990%3A%20Ershad%20resigns%20after%20protests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20wave%20of%20protests%20calling%20for%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20Ershad%20resigned%20as%20president%20on%20December%206%2C%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20then%20arrested%20on%20December%2012%20and%20jailed%20after%20being%20convicted%20for%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Minister%20Shahabuddin%20Ahmed%20took%20over%20as%20interim%20leader%20until%20elections%20could%20be%20held%20the%20year%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EErshad%20would%20eventually%20be%20released%20in%20January%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1991%3A%20First%20free%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20first%20free%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20early%201991%2C%20with%20the%20Bangladesh%20Nationalist%20Party%20(BNP)%20running%20out%20as%20clear%20winners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhaleda%20Zia%2C%20General%20Ziaur%20Rahman's%20widow%2C%20became%20Bangladesh's%20first%20woman%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20succeeded%20by%20her%20arch-rival%20Sheikh%20Hasina%2C%20daughter%20of%20the%20country's%20founding%20father%20Mujibur%20Rahman%2C%20after%20Hasina's%20Awami%20League%20beat%20the%20BNP%20at%20the%20ballot%20box%20in%201996.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BNP%20returned%20to%20power%20in%202001%2C%20with%20Zia%20once%20again%20becoming%20prime%20minister%20and%20completing%20her%20term%20of%20office%20in%20October%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2007%3A%20Anti-corruption%20purge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20with%20the%20army's%20support%2C%20President%20Iajuddin%20Ahmed%20declared%20a%20state%20of%20emergency%20after%20anti-government%20demonstrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20military-led%20transitional%20government%20then%20launched%20an%20anti-corruption%20purge%2C%20imprisoning%20both%20Hasina%20and%20Zia%20on%20graft%20allegations%20before%20their%20release%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20party's%20win%20in%20the%20polls%20in%20December%202008%2C%20Hasina%20once%20again%20became%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20fe