and%20other%20companies%20to%20be%20their%20default%20search%20engine%20have%20violated%20antitrust%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-violated-antitrust-law-to-keep-search-monopoly-judge-rules-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20federal%20judge%20ruled%20on%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20is%20a%20monopolist%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20US%20District%20Judge%20Amit%20P.%20Mehta%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.lbr.cloud%2Fpublic%2F2024-08%2F045110819896.pdf%3FVersionId%3DmHMw8uSvPbFCwl.7.yAY8wRXM0.UCmrD%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20it%20has%20acted%20as%20one%20to%20maintain%20its%20monopoly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Justice's%20case%20centered%20on%20Google's%20payments%20to%20other%20companies%2C%20like%20Apple%20and%20Samsung%2C%20to%20give%20its%20search%20engine%20prominence%20on%20their%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Google%2C%20there's%20apparently%20a%20very%20good%20reason%20to%20keep%20these%20payments%20coming%2C%20as%20the%20search%20revenue%20generated%20is%20worth%20billions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Monday's%20filing%2C%20the%20company%20estimated%20in%202017%20that%20its%20default%20placements%20across%20Safari%2C%20Firefox%2C%20and%20other%20browsers%20drove%2054%25%20of%20its%20search%20revenue.%20That%20number%20has%20only%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20Google%20has%20a%20major%20deal%20with%20Apple%20to%20keep%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20Safari%2C%20which%20runs%20on%20iPhones%2C%20iPads%2C%20and%20Mac%20computers%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Google%20projected%20that%20it%20would%20lose%20between%2060%25%20and%2080%25%20of%20its%20search%20volume%20on%20Apple%20devices%20if%20it%20were%20replaced%20as%20the%20default%20general%20search%20engine%2C%20the%20filing%20said.%20That%20accounts%20for%20between%20%2428.2%20bi