%20the%20family's%20insistence%2C%20his%20US-based%20son%20and%20former%20Chief%20Advisor%20Sajeeb%20Wajed%20Joy%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20wanted%20to%20stay%2C%20she%20did%20not%20want%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20at%20all.%20But%20we%20kept%20insisting%20that%20it%20wasn't%20safe%20for%20her.%20We%20were%20concerned%20for%20her%20physical%20safety%20first%3B%20so%20we%20persuaded%20her%20to%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20son%20Joy%20told%20NDTV's%20Marya%20Shakil%20in%20a%20telephonic%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20spoke%20to%20her%20this%20morning.%20The%20situation%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20as%20you%20can%20see%2C%20is%20anarchy.%20She%20is%20in%20good%20spirits%20but%20she%20is%20very%20disappointed.%20It's%20very%20disheartening%20for%20her%20because%20it%20was%20her%20dream%20to%20turn%20Bangladesh%20into%20a%20developed%20country%20and%20she%20worked%20so%20hard%20for%20it%20over%20the%20last%2015%20years%2C%20keeping%20it%20safe%20from%20militants%20and%20as%20well%20as%20from%20terrorism%20and%20in%20spite%20of%20all%20of%20that%20this%20vocal%20minority%2C%20the%20opposition%2C%20the%20militants%20have%20now%20seized%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20flight%20came%20less%20than%20seven%20months%20after%20she%20celebrated%20a%20fourth%20straight%20term%20in%20power%20-%20and%20fifth%20overall%20-%20by%20sweeping%20national%20elections%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2076-year-old%20was%20flown%20in%20a%20military%20helicopter%20on%20Monday%20with%20her%20sister%20to%20take%20refuge%20in%20India.%20She%20is%20expected%20to%20leave%20for%20London%20later%2C%20sources%20told%20NDTV%2C%20where%20she%20may%20seek%20political%20asylum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20son%2C%20however%2C%20said%20he%20did%20not%20discuss%20with%20her%20where%20she%20is%20headed%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20last%2015%20years%20in%20power%20were%20marked%20by%20arrests%20of%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20crackdowns%20on%20free%20speech%20and%20suppression%20of%20dissent%2C%20and%20she%20resigned%20in%20the%20face%20of%20deadly%20student-led%20protests%20that%20have%20killed%20hundreds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtests%20began%20in%20June%20after%20student%20groups'%20demands%20for%20the%20scrapping%20of%20a%20controversial%20quota%20system%20in%20government%20jobs%20escalated%20into%20a%20movement%20seeking%20the%20end%20of%20her%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20hope%20that%20there%20will%20be%20elections%20in%20Bangladesh%20but%20at%20this%20time%20with%20our%20party%20leaders%20being%20targeted%20I%20don't%20see%20how%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20would%20be%20possible.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20it%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20family's%20responsibility.%20We%20have%20shown%20what%20we%20can%20do.%20We%20have%20shown%20How%20much%20we%20can%20develop%20Bangladesh%20and%20if%20the%20people%20of%20Bangladesh%20aren't%20willing%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20let%20this%20violent%20minority%20seize%20power%20then%20people%20get%20the%20leadership%20they%20deserve%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20his%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPressed%20to%20answer%20if%20his%20mother%20did%20the%20best%20for%20the%20country%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAbsolutely.%20Awami%20League%20still%20remains%20the%20most%20popular%20party%20in%20the%20country.%20BNP%20has%20the%20chance%20to%20come%20back%20to%20power%20and%20we%20have%20seen%20what%20they%20were%20like%20the%20last%20time.%20They%20ran%20the%20country%20to%20the%20ground.%20The%20militants%20had%20a%20free%20hand%3B%20they%20attacked%20the%20minorities%20with%20impunity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladeshi%20President%20Mohammed%20Shahabuddin%20ordered%20the%20release%20of%20jailed%20former%20prime%20minister%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbangladesh-president-orders-release-of-jailed-ex-pm-khaleda-zia-6270786%5C%22%3Ekey%20opposition%20leader%20Khaleda%20Zia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hours%20after%20her%20arch-rival%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20was%20ousted%20and%20the%20military%20took%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh's%20army%20chief%20General%20Waker-Uz-Zaman%20said%20in%20a%20broadcast%20to%20the%20nation%20on%20state%20television%20that%20Hasina%20had%20resigned%20and%20the%20military%20would%20form%20a%20caretaker%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20country%20has%20suffered%20a%20lot%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20been%20hit%2C%20many%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20--%20it%20is%20time%20to%20stop%20the%20violence%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Waker%2C%20shortly%20after%20jubilant%20crowds%20stormed%20and%20looted%20Hasina's%20official%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh's%20Channel%2024%20broadcast%20images%20of%20crowds%20running%20into%20the%20prime%20minister's%20compound%2C%20grinning%20and%20waving%20to%20the%20camera%2C%20looting%20furniture%20and%20books%2C%20or%20relaxing%20on%20beds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20military%20said%20it%20would%20lift%20a%20curfew%20imposed%20to%20quash%20protests%20at%20dawn%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20doubt%20army%20will%20be%20able%20to%20normalise%20things%20that%20fast.%20Because%20right%20now%20what%20is%20happening%20is%20that%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20militants%2C%20they%20are%20not%20only%20vandalising%2C%20they%20are%20also%20hunting%20out%20our%20leaders%2C%20former%20ministers%20and%20even%20what%20I%20am%20hearing%20minorties.%20I%20don't%20think%20the%20violence%20has%20ended%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Joy.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMobs%20raided%20and%20ransacked%20the%20homes%20of%20Hasina's%20Awami%20League%20party%20allies%20as%20well%20as%20police%20stations%2C%20witnesses%20told%20news%20agency%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrowds%20smashed%20statues%20of%20her%20father%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%2C%20the%20country's%20independence%20hero%2C%20and%20set%20fire%20to%20a%20museum%20dedicated%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20emotion%20is%20one%20of%20disappointment%2C%20anger%2C%20that%20my%20grandfather%20liberated%20the%20country%20and%20they%20killed%20him%20and%20my%20entire%20family.%20And%20now%20the%20same%20powers%2C%20these%20are%20the%20minorities%20that%20opposed%20the%20independence%20of%20Bangladesh%20are%20using%20this%20opportunity%20to%20basically%20deny%20and%20destroy%20our%20hard-fought%20struggle%20for%20freedom.%20And%20it's%20very%20disheartening%20to%20see%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20Bangladesh%20is%20staying%20silent%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Joy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20south%20Asian%20nation%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20coups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20military%20declared%20an%20emergency%20in%20January%202007%20after%20widespread%20political%20unrest%20and%20installed%20a%20military-backed%20caretaker%20government%20for%20two%20years.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722883440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fsct30qqg_bangladesh-crisis-_625x300_05_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshe-didnt-want-to-leave-we-insisted-sheikh-hasinas-son-to-ndtv-6271386%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sheikh%20Hasina%2C%20who%20resigned%20as%20Bangladesh's%20prime%20minister%20and%20fled%20the%20country%20on%20Monday%20following%20weeks%20of%20protests%2C%20did%20not%20want%20to%20leave%20at%20all%20but%20did%20so%20on%20the%20family's%20insistence%2C%20his%20US-based%20son%20told%20NDTV.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshe-didnt-want-to-leave-we-insisted-sheikh-hasinas-son-to-ndtv-6271386%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshe-didnt-want-to-leave-we-insisted-sheikh-hasinas-son-to-ndtv-6271386%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshe-didnt-want-to-leave-we-insisted-sheikh-hasinas-son-to-ndtv-6271386%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Unstable%20Bangladesh%20Can%20Lead%20To%20%26quot%3BVolcanic%20Eruption%26quot%3B%2C%20Says%20Nobel%20Laureate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERestoration%20of%20law%20and%20order%20is%20the%20biggest%20issue%20facing%20Bangladesh%20now%20and%20if%20that%20cannot%20be%20achieved%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20spillover%20effect%20in%20neighbouring%20countries%20including%20India%2C%20Muhammad%20Yunus%2C%20Nobel%20laureate%20and%20founder%20of%20Grameen%20Bank%2C%20told%C2%A0%20NDTV%20in%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20today.%20Now%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20has%20been%20ousted%2C%20the%20situation%20has%20taken%20a%20turn%20for%20the%20better%20and%20the%20country%20has%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20celebratory%20mood%20doesn't%20turn%20ugly.%20People%20should%20get%20back%20home%20after%20celebrations%20and%20it%20should%20be%20business%20as%20usual%20from%20morning%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20weeks%20of%20massive%20turmoil%20in%20the%20country%2C%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20top%20job%20today%2C%20following%20a%2045-minute%20ultimatum%20from%20the%20army.%20She%20is%20currently%20in%20India%20but%20it%20is%20not%20known%20what%20her%20final%20destination%20is.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20rampage%20of%20protesters%20continued%20despite%20her%20exit.%20The%20clashes%20that%20followed%20were%20between%20the%20protesters%20and%20the%20supporters%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20Awami%20League.%20Late%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20protesters%20entered%20and%20ransacked%C2%A0%20Gono%20Bhaban%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20official%20residence.%20The%20statue%20of%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%2C%20Ms%20Hasina's%20father%20and%20the%20tallest%20leader%20in%20the%20country's%20history%20who%20led%20its%20fight%20for%20Independence%20from%20Pakistan%20was%20vandalised.%20The%20house%20of%20a%20minister%20was%20also%20set%20on%20fire.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20who%20was%20controlling%20the%20protesters%20and%20how%20serious%20the%20consequences%20can%20be%20if%20they%20cannot%20be%20brought%20under%20control%2C%C2%A0%20Mr%20Yunus%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bwould%20not%20be%20a%20very%20happy%20situation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20destabilise%20Bangladesh%2C%20it%20will%20spill%20over%20all%20around%20Bangladesh%2C%20including%20Myanmar%20and%20seven%20sisters%20in%20West%20Bengal%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20a%20volcanic%20eruption%20everywhere%20around%20us%20and%20in%20Myanmar...%20and%20it%20would%20be%20a%20bigger%20problem%20because%20a%20million%20Rohingyas%20are%20in%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20the%20situation%2C%20he%20said%20there%20are%20170%20million%20people%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20young%20people%20who%20never%20voted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20are%20happy%20and%20law%20abiding%20citizens%20and%20they%20know%20there's%20a%20democracy...%20These%20young%20people%20never%20voted%20in%20their%20life.%20They%20never%20went%20to%20the%20polling%20booth%20because%20those%20elections%20were%20never%20held...%20Our%20starting%20point%20is%20we%20have%20to%20get%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20young%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20is%20currently%20under%20the%20control%20of%20its%20army%2C%20which%20has%20given%20assurances%20of%20a%20peaceful%20solution.%20Army%20chief%20General%20Waker-Uz-Zaman%20has%20told%20the%20media%20that%20the%20Army%20will%20form%20an%20interim%20government%20with%20advice%20from%20the%20President.%20He%20has%20also%20appealed%20to%20the%20protesters%20to%20help%20restore%20peace%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20300%20people%20have%20died%20in%20the%20violence%20that%20has%20been%20continuing%20since%20last%20month.%20The%20protests%20had%20i