0the%20title%20of%20the%20first%20Indian%20table%20tennis%20player%20to%20reach%20Olympics%20pre-quarterfinals%2C%20Manika%20reflected%20through%20a%20post%20on%20Instagram%2C%20%E2%80%9CReaching%20the%20pre-quarterfinals%20of%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Singles%20in%20Olympics%20has%20been%20a%20milestone%2C%20but%20I%20always%20want%20more.%20As%20long%20as%20I%20have%20a%20dream%2C%20an%20aim%2C%20I%20will%20keep%20doing%20my%20best.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2029-year-old%20hails%20from%20Delhi%20and%20is%20the%20youngest%20of%20three%20siblings.%20At%20the%20young%20age%20of%20four%2C%20she%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20sport%20by%20her%20sister%2C%20Aanchal%2C%20and%20brother%20Sahil%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20also%20played%20table%20tennis.%20It%20became%20clear%20that%20she%20was%20destined%20for%20greatness%20when%20she%20won%20a%20state-level%20under-8%20tournament%2C%20prompting%20her%20to%20train%20under%20coach%20Sandeep%20Gupta%20at%20Hans%20Raj%20Model%20School.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManika%E2%80%99s%20rise%20to%20fame%20began%20with%20a%20silver%20medal%20in%20the%20under-21%20category%20at%20the%202011%20Chile%20Open.%20She%20also%20achieved%20quarterfinal%20finishes%20while%20representing%20India%20at%20the%202014%20Commonwealth%20Games%20in%20Glasgow%20and%20the%202014%20Asian%20Games.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20breakthrough%20arrived%20at%20the%202015%20Commonwealth%20Table%20Tennis%20Championships%2C%20where%20she%20won%20three%20medals%2C%20including%20silver%20in%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20team%20and%20doubles%20events%20and%20bronze%20in%20singles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20her%20achievements%2C%20Manika%20grew%20up%20hearing%2C%20%E2%80%9CTable%20tennis%20is%20a%20waste%20of%20time%2C%20be%20a%20doctor%20or%20engineer%20instead.%E2%80%9D%20Growing%20up%20in%20Delhi%2C%20her%20relatives%20taunted%20her%20for%20choosing%20sports%20as%20a%20career.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F186746%2Fdaughter-of-farm-labourers-beat-all-odds-to-win-asian-games-gold-for-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBut%20her%20mother%2C%20Sushma%20Batra%2C%20had%20full%20faith%20in%20her%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20dream%20to%20play%20for%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20her%20father%20is%20her%20cheerleader.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20limited%20means%2C%20they%20struggled%20to%20afford%20the%20equipment%20and%20make%20the%20arrangements%20for%20tournaments%2C%20yet%20her%20mother%20kept%20encouraging%20Manika.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20asked%20me%20why%20she%20is%20wasting%20her%20time%20in%20sport%2C%20but%20I%20always%20thought%20that%20sports%20had%20potential.%20She%20has%20proven%20me%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20her%20mother%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC-E8eaCI5mu%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC-E8eaCI5mu%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC-E8eaCI5mu%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20The%20Better%20India%20(%40thebetterindia)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202018%20Asian%20Games%20saw%20Manika%20secure%20three%20gold%20medals%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20team%20events.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20she%20qualified%20for%20the%20Rio%20Olympics%20but%20was%20defeated%20in%20the%20first%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManika%E2%80%99s%20most%20significant%20achievement%20came%20at%20the%202018%20Commonwealth%20Games%20in%20Gold%20Coast%2C%20Australia%2C%20where%20she%20led%20India%20to%20a%20historic%20gold%20medal%20in%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20team%20event%2C%20defeating%20the%20dominant%20Singapore%20team.%20She%20also%20won%20India%E2%80%99s%20first-ever%20silver%20medal%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles%20and%20claimed%20a%20monumental%20gold%20in%20the%20singles%20event%2C%20bringing%20home%20four%20medals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20she%20was%20honoured%20with%20the%20Arjuna%20Award%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20second-highest%20sporting%20honour.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20in%202020%2C%20she%20achieved%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20national%20sports%20recognition%20by%20receiving%20the%20Khel%20Ratna%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20highest%20sporting%20honour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20subsequent%20years%2C%20Manika%20continued%20her%20success%2C%20winning%20team%20gold%20at%20the%202019%20Commonwealth%20Table%20Tennis%20Championships.%20Her%20achievement%20of%20becoming%20the%20first%20paddler%20to%20reach%20round%20of%2016%20surpasses%20her%20previous%20record%20at%20the%20Tokyo%20Olympics%2C%20where%20she%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20women%E2%80%99s%20table%20tennis%20player%20to%20reach%20the%20round%20of%2032%20in%20singles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20Tokyo%20Games%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F293449%2Fsharath-kamal-table-tennis-player-at-men-single-commonwealth-games-father-dream%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAchanta%20Sharath%20Kamal%20had%20also%20reached%20the%20round%20of%2032%20in%20the%20men%E2%80%99s%20singles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20won%20the%20WTT%20Contender%20Budapest%20mixed%20doubles%20and%20the%20WTT%20Contender%20Lasko%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles.%20She%20competed%20in%20the%20inaugural%20WTT%20Grand%20Smash%20event%20in%20Singapore%20in%202022%20and%20achieved%20a%20career-high%20ranking%20of%20world%20number%20four%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles%20with%20Archana%20Girish%20Kamath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManika%20aspires%20to%20do%20for%20table%20tennis%20in%20India%20what%20PV%20Sindhu%20and%20Saina%20Nehwal%20did%20for%20badminton%20in%20the%20country.%20%E2%80%9CLike%20table%20tennis%2C%20badminton%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20so%20famous%20(in%20India)%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Folympics.com%2Fen%2Fathletes%2Fmanika-batra%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManika%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20amount%20of%20recognition%20they%20have%20got%20for%20the%20sport%2C%20I%20would%20also%20like%20to%20take%20table%20tennis%20to%20greater%20heights%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhilst%20table%20tennis%20was%20her%20first%20love%2C%20Manika%20turned%20down%20modelling%20offers%20in%20her%20teens%20to%20concentrate%20on%20the%20sport.%20Her%20dedication%20has%20not%20only%20brought%20her%20personal%20success%20but%20has%20also%20inspired%20a%20generation%20of%20young%20table%20tennis%20players%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20laurels%20indeed%20make%20her%20a%20true%20icon%20of%20Indian%20table%20tennis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722849309000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D359739%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Khel%