%3ENara%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eare%20festooned%20with%20animal%20fur%20too.%20The%20backpack%20contains%20a%20%3Cem%3Edao%20%3C%2Fem%3E(machete)%2C%20a%20sword%20whose%20cover%20is%20made%20of%20monkey%20skin%2C%20a%20spear%2C%20and%20arrows.%20The%20backpack%20is%20slung%20across%20the%20shoulder%20by%20a%20strap%20made%20of%20bearskin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jewellery%20meanwhile%20includes%20tiger%20nails%2C%20jaws%20of%20the%20tiger%20and%20clouded%20leopard%20%E2%80%94%20both%20%E2%80%98vulnerable%E2%80%99%20according%20to%20the%20IUCN%2C%20and%20teeth%20of%20the%20wild%20boar.%20Nabam%20points%20out%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20Nyishi%20tribe%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F278791%2Fwomen-led-deepa-pawar-anubhuti-uplifts-nomadic-tribes-rights-mental-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20other%20tribes%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20don%20accessories%20made%20out%20of%20animal%20parts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20shares%20that%20the%20parts%20play%20more%20than%20a%20perfunctory%20role.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20jaws%20of%20the%20tiger%20and%20clouded%20leopard%20are%20worn%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3ENyub%20%3C%2Fem%3E(priest)%20and%20%3Cem%3ENyagam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(orator).%20They%20signify%20importance.%20Since%20the%20tiger%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20wearing%20its%20teeth%20indicates%20high%20status%20in%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20teeth%20and%20nails%20of%20tigers%20are%20worn%20to%20enhance%20the%20attire%20and%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20importance.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2